
Note that galaxies with redshifts obtained from nearest galaxies 
with ^{0.1}M_r-5\log h \le -22.5 -- (Petro or Model) ,(K+E corrected to z=0.1)
are not included.
* For early-type galaxy with c=r90/r50>2.6, Petro magnitude is applied
mag=mag-0.1 (according to Bell et al. 2003)
* All the absolute magnitudes are now converted to WMAP3 cosmology.
* Note that the last 30 galaxies did not fulfill our first selections, by are 
  central galaxies of ROSAT X-ray clusters. We add these galaxies for completeness.

SDSS7_INFO: (extracted from NYU VAGC)

col  1: galaxy ID
col  2: NYU-VAGC ID : object ID (row in NYU-VAGC files)
col  3: redshift source type: 1 SDSS; 2 other; 3 KSG-VAGC; 4 nearest (negtive for parent); 5 needed by ROSAT X-ray
col  4: velocity dispersion: VDISP
col  5: error in velocity dispersion: VDISP_ERR
col  6-10: AB magnitudes in u,g,r,i,z bands -- Petro (negative values: negative flux)
col  11-15: absolute magnitudes in u,g,r,i,z bands (K-corrected to z=0.1) -- Petro
col  16-20: AB magnitudes in u,g,r,i,z bands -- model (negative values: negative flux)
col  21-25: absolute magnitudes in u,g,r,i,z bands (K-corrected to z=0.1) -- model

 (Note evolution is not included, can be added according to Blanton et al. 2004)

SDSS7_ST: (extracted from NYU VAGC)

col  1: galaxy ID
col  2: NYU-VAGC ID : object ID (row in NYU-VAGC files)
col  3: log10 M*/ h^{-2}\msun based on petro magnitudes (using Bell 2003)
col  4: log10 M*/ h^{-2}\msun based on model magnitudes (using Bell 2003)
col  5: sersic_n 
col  6: sersic_r0
col  7: r50: PETROR50
col  8: r90: PETROR90
col  9: redshift source type: 1 SDSS; 2 other; 3 KSG-VAGC; 4 nearest (negtive for parent), 5 needed by ROAST X-ray




